### Settled implementation decisions (slice 1)

- **Q1 — signup-tx seed mechanics:** inline in `signupOwner`, mirroring
  the Phase-1 class-level precedent, using extracted constants from a new
  `packages/db/src/seeds/grading.ts`. Scheme via `upsert` (need its id to
  attach components + retry-idempotency against `@@unique([schoolId])`);
  components + boundaries via `createMany({ skipDuplicates: true })`. NOT a
  separate tx-taking helper (keeps the GUC/tx-sharing subtlety visible at
  the one call site). Seed writes NO separate audit row — piggybacks
  `auth.signup_owner`, same as the class-level seed.
- **Q1 sub-decision (FLAGGED → my lean APPROVED): INCLUDE the idempotent
  backfill** for existing schemeless schools in the slice-1 migration. The
  migration role (`school_kit`) is a superuser → bypasses FORCE RLS, so the
  cross-school backfill INSERTs need no GUC. `NOT EXISTS` guards keep it
  idempotent on re-`migrate deploy`. Removes the slice-2 footgun (scores
  depend on a scheme existing).
- **Q2 — sum-to-100 enforcement:** service-layer (load-bearing, covers
  single PATCH/DELETE re-validation) + Zod `.superRefine` on the bulk PUT
  for bindable UX. **No Postgres trigger** (consistent with Phase-1
  deferring the enrollment CHECK+trigger to service-layer). Refine issues
  bind to a real path `['components']` — never bare object-level with empty
  `path:[]` (the class-arm `as never` lesson).
- **Q3 — boundary tile-0-100:** same shape; service-layer primary + Zod
  superRefine binding issues to per-row paths `['boundaries', i, 'maxScore']`.
- **Q4 — settings UI form-class discipline (cp2):** confirmed — local
  FormValues schema (not the API body schema), root + per-field error
  blocks, ''→undefined on submit, zero `as never`. Highest-risk form class
  in the slice (numeric weight/min/max = the exact class-arm break combo).
- **Q5 (FLAGGED → my lean APPROVED): 2 cps as scoped** (cp1 = API
  foundation, cp2 = settings UI). cp1a/cp1b split is the NAMED fallback —
  invoke SCOPE GUARD mid-build only if cp1 actually balloons; do not
  pre-split.

### Slice-1-era RBAC pattern (important divergence noted)

Phase-1 controllers now carry `@Permissions` + `PermissionsGuard` (retrofit
landed in slice 13). Per the approved plan I mirror the **slice-1-ERA**
shape, not today's: grading controller uses `@UseGuards(AuthGuard)` ONLY,
and the service gates via `assertUserActiveAndHasOneOf(['owner','admin'])`.
`PHASE_2_SLICE_1_PERMISSIONS` lands as a **reference-only** const (NOT in
`ALL_PERMISSIONS`, NOT wired to the guard or admin seed). Slice 9 retrofits
`PermissionsGuard` + `@Permissions` exactly as slice 13 did for Phase 1 —
this keeps admins able to use the settings UI during slices 1–8 (they have
no grading perms yet; owner passes via `*`).

